PREFACE

In some cases, only the initials of the bride or the groom (or both) are shown on the marriage records.

A search was made by the compilers of this book, and wherever possible, initials have been replaced by full and correct names, enabling the reader to more easily identify the parties.

Sources used include the following: Jean C. & Wendell C. Tombaugh, Fulton County, Indiana, Cemetery Inscriptions, Vols 1 through 4; Jean C. & Wendell C. Tombaugh, Fulton County, Indiana, Wills (Briefed) 1836-1974; Wendell C. Tombaugh, Fulton County, Indiana, Newspaper Excerpts, 1858-1864; 1865-1868; 1869-1871; Various other newspaper obituaries (unpublished by Jean C. & Wendell C. Tombaugh); Jean C. & Wendell C. Tombaugh, Fulton County Indiana Census (1850; 1860; 1870; 1880); Wendell C. Tombaugh, Fulton County, Indiana, School Enumeration (26 vols 1896-1925); Fulton County, Indiana, Marriage Applications (May 29, 1892 - Feb 24, 1898; Jan 2, 1901 - Oct 30, 1904; Nov 3, 1904 - Nov 26, 1910).

Books Numbered as Follows:

(1) = Oct 2, 1836 - Jan 20, 1850

A through J = Jan 20, 1850 - Dec 31, 1922

1 through 19 = Jan 8, 1923 - Oct 22, 1983

Abbreviations:

(A) = Application

(L) = License

(V) = Void

JCT & WCT

February 1, 1985
